		Key West Women’s March 
	





                    By Florida Weekly Staff                


on 
                    February 06, 2020                







 
The public was invited to join the Florida Keys chapter of Women’s March Florida for a nonpartisan, peaceful, family-friendly gathering at the unity march down Duval Street to the downtown Mallory Square. At the post-march rally, participants heard from powerful speakers, including U.S. Rep. Debbie Mucarsel-Powell, and demonstrated their commitment to equity, tolerance, human rights and justice for all. This year, the group marched in defense of reproductive rights, immigrant families and our planet.
